<div class=Section1 style='layout-grid:15.6pt'>

<h1 style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:30.0pt;line-height:
240%;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;font-weight:normal'>How To
Install Linux, nginx, MySQL, PHP (LEMP)&nbsp; </span></h1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='line-height:22.5pt;background:white'><span
class=tutorial-date><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:#B5B5B5'>&nbsp;</span></span></p>

<h3 style='margin-top:10.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:8.25pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
16.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:-.4pt'>About
Lemp</span></h3>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>LEMP stack is a
group of open source software to get web servers up and running. The acronym
stands for Linux, nginx (pronounced Engine x), MySQL, and PHP. Since the server
is already running Ubuntu, the linux part is taken care of. Here is how to
install the rest.</span></p>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Setup</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>The steps in
this tutorial require the user to have root privileges. You can see how to set
that up in the<a
href="https://www.digitalocean.com/community/articles/initial-server-setup-with-ubuntu-12-04"
style='box-sizing: border-box'><span style='color:black'>Initial Server Setup
Tutorial</span></a><span class=apple-converted-space>&nbsp;</span>in steps 3
and 4.</span></p>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step One - Update Apt-Get</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Throughout this
tutorial we will be using apt-get as an installer for all the server programs.
On May 8th, 2012, a serious php vulnerability was discovered, and it is
important that we download all of the latest patched software to protect the
virtual private server.</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Let's do a
thorough update.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo apt-get update</span></pre>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step Two - Install MySQL</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>MySQL is a
powerful database management system used for organizing and retrieving data</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>To install
MySQL, open terminal and type in these commands:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo apt-get install mysql-server php5-mysql</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>During the
installation, MySQL will ask you to set a root password. If you miss the chance
to set the password while the program is installing, it is very easy to set the
password later from within the MySQL shell.</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:
"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Once you're done with that you can finish up
by installing PHP.</span></p>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step Three - Install nginx</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Once MySQL is
all set up, we can move on to installing nginx on the VPS.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>echo &quot;deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/nginx/stable/ubuntu $(lsb_release -sc) main&quot; | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/nginx-stable.list</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>sudo apt-key adv --keyserver keyserver.ubuntu.com --recv-keys C300EE8C</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>sudo apt-get update</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>sudo apt-get install nginx</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>nginx does not
start on its own. To get nginx running, type:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo service nginx start</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>You can confirm
that nginx has installed an your web server by directing your browser to your
IP address.</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>You can run the
following command to reveal your VPS's IP address.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>ifconfig eth0 | grep inet | awk '{ print $2 }'</span></pre>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step Four - Install PHP</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>To install
PHP-FPM, open terminal and type in these commands. We will configure the
details of nginx and php details in the next step:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo apt-get install php5-fpm</span></pre>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step Five - Configure php</span></h2>

<p class=MsoNormal style='background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
14.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>We need to make one small
change in the php configuration.Open up php.ini:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:21.0pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:
"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;sudo nano /etc/php5/fpm/php.ini</span></pre>

<p class=MsoNormal style='background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
14.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Find the line,
cgi.fix_pathinfo=1, and change the 1 to 0.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:21.0pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:
"Courier New";color:black'>cgi.fix_pathinfo=0</span></pre>

<p class=MsoNormal style='background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
14.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>If this number is kept as
1, the php interpreter will do its best to process the file that is as near to
the requested file as possible. This is a possible security risk. If this
number is set to 0, conversely, the interpreter will only process the exact
file path - a much safer alternative. Save and Exit. We need to make another
small change in the php5-fpm configuration.Open up www.conf:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:21.0pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:
"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;sudo nano /etc/php5/fpm/pool.d/www.conf</span></pre>

<p class=MsoNormal style='background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
14.5pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Find the line, listen =
127.0.0.1:9000, and change the 127.0.0.1:9000 to /var/run/php5-fpm.sock.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:21.0pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:
"Courier New";color:black'>listen = /var/run/php5-fpm.sock</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Save and Exit.</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Restart
php-fpm:</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo service php5-fpm restart</span></pre>

<h2 style='margin-top:7.5pt;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:
21.0pt;font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:#2D2D2D;letter-spacing:.15pt;
font-weight:normal'>Step Six - Configure nginx</span></h2>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Open up the
default virtual host file.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>The
configuration should include the changes below (the details of the changes are
under the config information):</span></p>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><strong
style='box-sizing: border-box'><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";
color:black'>UPDATE:</span></strong><span class=apple-converted-space><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></span><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Newer Ubuntu
versions create a directory called 'html' instead of 'www' by default. If
/usr/share/nginx/www does not exist, it's probably called html. Make sure you
update your configuration appropriately.</span></p>

<pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box;
word-wrap: normal;border-radius: 3px;background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.0470588);
overflow:auto'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>&nbsp;[...]</span></pre><pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;
background:white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>server {</span></pre><pre style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:
white'><span lang=EN-US style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";
color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; listen&nbsp;&nbsp; 80;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; root /usr/share/nginx/www;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; index index.php index.html index.htm;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; server_name example.com;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; location / {</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; error_page 404 /404.html;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; error_page 500 502 503 504 /50x.html;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; location = /50x.html {</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; root /usr/share/nginx/www;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; }</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; # pass the PHP scripts to FastCGI server listening on the php-fpm socket</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; location ~ \.php$ {</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; try_files $uri =404;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fastcgi_pass unix:/var/run/php5-fpm.sock;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fastcgi_index index.php;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; fastcgi_param SCRIPT_FILENAME $document_root$fastcgi_script_name;</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; include fastcgi_params;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>}</span></pre><pre
style='margin-bottom:21.0pt;background:white'><span lang=EN-US
style='font-size:10.5pt;font-family:"Courier New";color:black'>[...]</span></pre>

<p style='margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:16.5pt;margin-left:
0cm;line-height:21.0pt;background:white;box-sizing: border-box'><span
lang=EN-US style='font-family:"Arial","sans-serif";color:black'>Save and Exit</span></p>

